manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Stream videos, play online games, and do other Internet activities simultaneously AC1200 Smart Wi-Fi Router (EA6100) At a Glance: Wireless-AC is faster than wireless-N for media streaming and more Dual wireless bands of 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz for fast data transfer speeds Four Ethernet ports for wired connections USB 2.0 port to connect devices across your network Smart Wi-Fi lets you remotely access and manage your network Linksys AC1200 Smart Wi-Fi Router (EA6100) Featuring wireless-AC technology and four Ethernet ports, the Linksys AC1200 Smart Wi-Fi Router is made for the well-connected home. It allows you to stream videos, play online games, and do other Internet activities simultaneously, on multiple devices. Dual bands and two external antennas provide an exceptionally strong, reliable wireless signal without dead spots. Four Ethernet ports provide connectivity to wired devices, while a USB 2.0 port lets you transfer files or share devices across your network. What's in the Box: Linksys AC1200 Smart Wi-Fi Router, Ethernet cable, power adapter, quick start guide, and CD-ROM with documentation

Wireless-AC Technology for Powerful Wi-Fi The Linksys AC1200 Smart Wi-Fi Router features high-speed wireless-AC technology along with dual wireless bands of 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz with speeds up to N300 Mbps + AC867 Mbps. The router enables data traffic to flow quickly and with minimal buffering so gaming, media streaming, and other Internet activities can occur simultaneously without interruptions or interference. Wireless-AC delivers speeds up to 2.8 times faster than wireless-N, making this router well suited for homes with multiple devices. Ethernet and USB 2.0 Ports for Wired Connections On the back of the AC1200 are four Ethernet ports that allow you to connect wired devices directly for Internet access as well as share data on external storage devices. The router also comes equipped with a USB 2.0 port, which allows you to transfer files or connect a printer to your network. For users who spend a lot of time transferring large files, such as HD videos, Linksys also offers an AC1200+ router. The AC1200+ has a USB 3.0 port and four Gigabit Ethernet ports that allow for super-fast transfer speeds over a wired connection. Wireless Security to Block Unauthorized Access The AC1200 features Wi-Fi Protected Setup along with WPA2 encryption and an SPI firewall to protect your data and keep your home Wi-Fi network secure. The router also allows you to create a dedicated network for guests and offers parental controls to limit access for children. Easy Setup without a CD Getting the AC1200 up and running is simple. Just plug the router into a power source, connect it to your Internet modem and your computer or laptop, connect to the Linksys secure network shown in the quick start guide, and follow the instructions. No installation CD is required.

Smart Wi-Fi Features Share Your Home Wi-Fi With Guests Using the app, you can create a separate guest network. Then, share the Wi-Fi password with your guests via text message or email. Set Boundaries with Parental Control Ensure a safe Internet experience for your kids even if you’re away from home. Use the app to restrict access to inappropriate content, control usage, and block specific devices from accessing the Internet. Prioritize Your Devices With Linksys Smart Wi-Fi, you can overcome bandwidth limitations and avoid lag by prioritizing devices that need the fastest Wi-Fi.

Compatibility Information Linksys Smart Wi-Fi is compatible with Android and iOS devices. Account information is confidential and only used to verify access to your home router settings. Customize and Manage Your Home Wi-Fi Anytime, Anywhere with Smart Wi-Fi This easy-to-use app places a powerful suite of Wi-Fi customization tools in the palm of your hand. Using the app, you can: See a real-time list of all connected devices Restrict access to inappropriate content Access advanced features to get the most out of your router Simplify network access
Set up your home Wi-Fi using a Linksys Smart Wi-Fi Router. Download the free Linksys Smart Wi-Fi App. Use Your Mobile Device to Manage Your Home Wi-Fi.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 3, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So far, performing well.
reviews.reviewText: The product is excellent, and the "Smart Wifi" app is actually quite intuitive, and rather comprehensive, given the amount if improvements recently made to the SOHO level products. I am currently very limited, given that I will have to replace my Linsys "gigabit" cable modem, since their "gigabit" modem is only currently at 100Mbps. Linksys's tech support, on the other hand, leaves a great deal to be desired. All but one of the people to whom I spoke were HEAVILY accented, and at least half of their sentences either have to be repeated, or must be deciphered against their (obviously) far-eastern accents. So much for "American" companies, eh?Internal throughput appears to be nominal, and in accordance with the device's specs. I will see what happens, once I've received my new cable modem.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 2, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very good router.....
reviews.reviewText: Good adapter. Range is very good on both bands. I have solid signal all over the home - the previous 10 year old router was good but had some weak spots. The configuration is pretty simple - i am having problems working with two of them cascaded - one facing the internet, the other facing it. I am trying to build a DMZ where i can open a network to the world to place web servers and then put my secure nodes behind the second one. The assisted config does not work well setting this up. I am planning to reflash it with a third party software.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 12, 2020
reviews.reviewText: This item was received in it's original manufacturers carton - not a shipping box. The flaps on the front were actually open - someone had obviously opened it up and had a look inside (probably someone at our RV Park). The flaps were not even taped shut - fortunately the router, cable, and power cord, were still in the box.Easy to set up though, and had it on-line in less than 30 mins - works great!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good, cheap, reliable
reviews.reviewText: Performs well in my 2 bedroom apartment with about 12 devices; a ps4, an xbox, a roku, two phones, two laptops, a desktop and several wireless surveilance cameras. When everything is connected and going at once, it does bog down, but for the most part, you can have two gaming connections and a video stream all at once with no problems. Any more than that and loading times get bad. Not a bad router for the price, you definitely get what you pay for but I would buy it again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Does not do wireless bridging
reviews.reviewText: I had purchased this a year ago to work around an issue I had with my TiVo box. By the time I got it, the issue was resolved, so I kept it in its box and moved out of state with it. Now in a new house, I had an immediate need for it. One of my original reasons to purchase it is that I assumed that it would wirelessly bridge with my existing network, especially given its price tag.I've spent probably 2 hours working with the "Smart" setup, struggling the entire way, only to discover that the the Wireless Bridging option doesn't exist. (Including creating a new account, validating it, but now it doesn't recognize my name/pass, and, if I request "Forgot my Password", no email is sent.... How "smart" of you.). Presumably, I can bridge via Ethernet, which is pretty useless to me.So, back in the box it goes, and I'm off looking for a much more cheaper alternative....

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 21, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Not So Smart....and unreliable.
reviews.reviewText: NOT so smart or easy to set up. The directions were not easy to follow in the box and I am not a complete illiterate when setting up computer equipment. I ended up calling Linksys and paying for the 6 month tech support rather than the two weeks.I have had the product for 1 month and had 2 tech calls and 3 drops in wifi service already. It keeps losing the IP address among being difficult to set up. I spent 2 hours the first phone call with tech support, 1.25 hours with tech support the second time, and fixed it myself the third time about .5 hours (day of this review) and am considering a new router for the future after spending $90 between the router on Amazon and the $40 of tech support if this keeps up. I had an N300 Linksys at home before this that worked great and use Linksys at work and have not had this problem. I recommend finding another product. On a positive It does work well when it works.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 21, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Can't be beat for the price.
reviews.reviewText: Replaced an older Linksys N router that was on the fritz (It was over 5 years old, so I think I can say I got my money out of it)Since my wireless devices have also updated to benefit from the dual-band technologies, This was a clear choice. I am on a 10Mbps Cable connection, and I am getting every bit of that at the end devices. Data transfer between devices is extremely fast (No, sorry I have not ran an internal speed test) but I can say that it is noticeably faster than the old N router was when it was new.Great router for a great price point. I know that there are newer and faster models available. I also know they cost between 4 to 8 TIMES the price that this one does. I cannot comment if this will work for the power gamers, but for the Netflix streamers, the iPad gamers, and the VPN, Work at home IT Professionals... It works just fine!The set up was also the easiest that I have ever seen for a wireless device. I have personally set up thousands as a former Geek Squad (In home service) Double Agent.Yes, I drove the Geek Squad mobile!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I used this only once though for 3 days. I was selling my mother's home and needed a router that would work for a few days to give me wifi. Perfect fit.

Todo perfecto, lo conecté directamente al módem de Telmex y mejoró bastante la señal inalámbrica, incluso en un segundo nivel y a 10m de distancia. Lo conseguí a un super precio y el servicio de paquetería como siempre excelente.

Easy to set up; good range. Very satisfied.
